- Finally, because most leaders have a simplistic vision of human behaviour.
Issued from the great engineering schools, they have a mechanistic interpretation of psychology.
They adopt, by intellectual comfort, the old Behaviorist theory, reactivated recently by the "neurosciences" of the United States and widely disseminated, without their knowledge, by the educational institutes and the media.
